ntsb3387txt-1-5-5-0-8 The pilot acknowledged '...020.' 
ntsb3387txt-1-5-5-0-9 When the controller asked if the pilot could turn to a heading of 020 the pilot responded, 'I'm heading 220...' 
ntsb3387txt-1-5-5-0-7 The pilot asked for the heading and it was repeated by the controller. 
ntsb3387txt-1-5-5-0-5 The controller repeatedly instructed the pilot to '...turn 
ntsb3387txt-1-5-5-0-6 around...' and '...make a left turn around...' to a heading of 020 degrees. 
ntsb3387txt-1-5-5-0-3 Shortly thereafter, the pilot reported a loss of engine power. 
ntsb3387txt-1-5-5-0-13 The pilot's CFI stated he recommended instrument proficiency training to the pilot 6 months prior to the accident. 
ntsb3387txt-1-5-5-0-10 The airplane collided with terrain approximately 10 miles from the airport. 
ntsb3387txt-1-5-5-0-14 The airplane was in cruise flight in conditions conducive to serious icing at cruise power. 
ntsb3387txt-1-5-5-0-4 The pilot was advised the airport was at his 6 o'clock position and 5 miles. 
ntsb3387txt-1-5-5-0-12 The pilot was not current for IFR flight. 
ntsb3387txt-1-5-5-0-1 While en route, the pilot called ATC and amended his final destination. 
ntsb3387txt-1-5-5-0-2 The airplane was at 5,000 feet in the vicinity of the original destination when ATC instructed the pilot to climb and maintain 6,000. 
ntsb3387txt-1-5-5-0-11 Examination of the pilot's logbook revealed approximately 117 hours of flight experience in the 6 years prior to the accident. 
